Time Complexity:

Let n = length of string

    Single traversal → O(n)
    Building result → O(n)

Overall: O(n)


Space Complexity:

    Stack stores characters → O(n)
    StringBuilder → O(n)

Overall: O(n)


Approach:

1. Create a stack to store characters

2. Traverse the string:

   - If current character is '*':
     → Remove last character (pop from stack)

   - Else:
     → Push character into stack

3. After traversal:
   - Pop all characters from stack into StringBuilder

4. Reverse the result (since stack is LIFO)

5. Return final string




class Solution {
    public String removeStars(String s) {
        Stack<Character> st = new Stack<>();
        StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
        for(int i=0; i<s.length(); i++){
            if(s.charAt(i)=='*') st.pop();
            else st.push(s.charAt(i));
        }
        while(st.size()>0){
            sb.append(st.pop());
        }
        sb.reverse();

        return sb.toString();
    }
}
